backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_10578815\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104onw1665702852978_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/onw1665702852978_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/onw1665702852978_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"onw1665702852978\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                   \n Configure the Use of Translation Tables \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The default USYS library usually includes all the translation tables needed to interface with display and keyboard devices, so there is no need for special configuration.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"onw1665702852978__context_w2126ab1b5b1_w2127ab1b5_w2128ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"onw1665702852978__topic_d13871e1_d13872e1_d13873e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"onw1665702852978__p_d13874e1_d13875e1_d13876e1\">However, if you have defined your own translation tables for specific devices, you can specify the library that holds them.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"onw1665702852978__li_d6698e1_d6699e1_d6700e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you are not using a translation table from the USYS library, specify the library using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$VARIATION</span> setting.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"onw1665702852978__li_d6701e1_d6702e1_d6703e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, specify specific translation tables you want to use using the following assignment settings:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"onw1665702852978__li_d6704e1_d6705e1_d6706e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oma1720015839839.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oma1720015839839.html\" title=\"Presents the form on the screen as display-only.\">display</a>—set the display translation table\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"onw1665702852978__li_d6707e1_d6708e1_d6709e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zbn1665702665252.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zbn1665702665252.html\" title=\"Return or set the current keyboard translation table.\">$keyboard</a>—specify the keyboard translation table\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"onw1665702852978__li_d6710e1_d6711e1_d6712e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gfe1665702721892.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gfe1665702721892.html\" title=\"Set the default keyboard and display table name.\">$DEFAULT_TERM</a>—specify the default terminal setting to be used if the defined device translation table cannot be found.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btf1665702980888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Translation Tables</a><p>To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fcq1665703251101.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$VARIATION</a><p>Specify the library name for global objects needed by the application when the application starts. Libraries are typed, so each global object library can have the same name which functions as a shared namespace which can be specified by this setting.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_10578815\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_10578815\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configure the Use of Translation Tables Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configure the Use of Translation Tables The default USYS library usually includes all the translation tables needed to interface with display and keyboard devices, so there is no need for special configuration. However, if you have defined your own translation tables for specific devices, you can specify the library that holds them. If you are not using a translation table from the USYS library, specify the library using the $VARIATION setting. Optionally, specify specific translation tables you want to use using the following assignment settings: display —set the display translation table $keyboard —specify the keyboard translation table $DEFAULT_TERM —specify the default terminal setting to be used if the defined device translation table cannot be found. Related Links Translation Tables To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables. $VARIATION Specify the library name for global objects needed by the application when the application starts. Libraries are typed, so each global object library can have the same name which functions as a shared namespace which can be specified by this setting. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}